Eligible applicants. 


To be eligible for assistance from funds appropriated to the Bureau for the Higher Education Grant Program, an applicant
must: 
(a) Be an Indian as defined in Section 40.2; 
(b) Be admitted for enrollment as a student in an eligible institution; 
(c) Apply for all available campus-based aid in a timely manner. 
